<p class="nohelp">Ideas are the lifeblood of innovation. Try not to worry too much if an idea seems unreasonable, difficult or unimaginative.
In the early stages of the innovation process you want to promote your ability to think, and to develop novel concepts.</p>
<p class="nohelp">'If an idea at first does not seem absurd, then there is no hope for it' - Albert Einstein</p>